        <h1>Health Benefits of Fruits and Vegetables</h1>
        <p>Fruits and vegetables are essential components of a healthy diet. They are rich in vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants that promote overall health and well-being. Below are some examples of fruits and vegetables along with their health benefits:</p>

        <h2>Fruits</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Apple:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Rich in fiber, which aids digestion and promotes heart health.</li>
                    <li>Contains antioxidants that may reduce the risk of chronic diseases.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Banana:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Excellent source of potassium, which helps regulate blood pressure and muscle function.</li>
                    <li>Provides natural energy and replenishes electrolytes.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Vegetables</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Spinach:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>High in iron, which is essential for healthy blood and energy levels.</li>
                    <li>Rich in vitamins A and C, which support immune function and promote healthy skin.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Broccoli:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Contains sulforaphane, a compound that may have anticancer properties.</li>
                    <li>Excellent source of vitamin K, which is important for bone health and blood clotting.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Proteins</h2>
        <p>In addition to vitamins and minerals, fruits and vegetables also provide proteins, though in smaller amounts compared to meat and dairy products. Some examples of proteins in fruits and vegetables include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Avocado: Contains all essential amino acids, making it a complete protein source.</li>
            <li>Peas and Spinach: Rich in protein and fiber, which helps with digestion and weight management.</li>
        </ul>
